how shocked and hurt she was,</i>

38:47.660 --> 38:50.663
<i>a poor widow woman to be asked
to prostitute herself</i>

38:50.830 --> 38:53.207
<i>for a man whom
she had so much respect for.</i>

38:53.374 --> 38:55.418
<i>An indentured servant
could not marry,</i>

38:55.584 --> 38:57.086
<i>so how could he think</i>

38:57.253 --> 39:00.047
<i>to torment an ill-starred
transportee girl,</i>

39:00.214 --> 39:02.133
<i>she could not fathom.</i>

39:02.299 --> 39:05.177
A poor transportee girl
who's got feelings for you.

39:09.974 --> 39:12.309
Feelings that
you can't possibly return.

39:14.603 --> 39:15.646
Essie...

39:15.813 --> 39:18.983
<i>John Richardson found himself
going down on one knee</i>

39:19.150 --> 39:22.611
<i>and proposing
an end to her indenture.</i>

39:23.779 --> 39:26.574
♪ You're my love

39:26.741 --> 39:29.118
♪ You're my angel

39:29.285 --> 39:31.203
♪ You're the girl... ♪

39:31.370 --> 39:33.998
<i>Until he had taken
her hand in marriage,</i>

39:34.165 --> 39:37.877
<i>Essie did not so much as kiss
Master Richardson.</i>

39:38.044 --> 39:41.881
<i>But when he did, she did,</i>

39:42.048 --> 39:45.259
<i>and from that day on,
she called him John.</i>

39:45.426 --> 39:48.220
♪ Daddy's home

39:50.097 --> 39:52.808
♪ Daddy's home

39:53.851 --> 39:55.227
♪ To stay... ♪

39:55.394 --> 39:57.480
<i>They called their son
the same.</i>

40:01.609 --> 40:04.612
<i>When the children went off to school
to learn their letters,</i>

40:04.779 --> 40:06.572
<i>Essie made sure
that each of them</i>

40:06.739 --> 40:08.532
<i>carried a little salt
in one pocket,</i>

40:08.699 --> 40:10.326
<i>a little bread in the other,</i>

40:10.493 --> 40:13.871
<i>to make sure they came safely home
once more.</i>

40:14.038 --> 40:16.749
<i>They always did.</i>

40:16.916 --> 40:19.460
♪ You had teardrops... ♪

40:19.627 --> 40:23.380
<i>John Richardson
loved her kindly.</i>

40:23.547 --> 40:24.965
♪ Daddy's home... ♪

40:25.132 --> 40:26.717
<i>They had been married a decade</i>

40:26.884 --> 40:31.639
<i>when Essie swore she heard
a banshee keen in the night.</i>

40:31.806 --> 40:35.810
<i>A week later,
the fever carried him off.</i>

40:41.023 --> 40:44.568
♪ It wasn't

40:44.735 --> 40:48.489
♪ On a Sunday

40:48.656 --> 40:51.700
♪ Monday and Tuesday went by

40:51.867 --> 40:58.124
♪ It wasn't
on a Tuesday afternoon

40:58.290 --> 41:01.919
♪ All I could do was cry

41:03.045 --> 41:05.881
♪ But I made a promise

41:06.048 --> 41:10.010
