come harvest time.

48:34.162 --> 48:37.082
If you are who I think you are,

48:37.249 --> 48:39.793
I have no quarrel with you.

48:40.836 --> 48:42.754
Nor I with you.

48:43.839 --> 48:45.757
Although it was you
that brought me here,

48:45.924 --> 48:48.218
you and a few others like you.

48:48.385 --> 48:50.512
Into this land
with no time for magic,

48:50.679 --> 48:53.098
no place for faeries
and such folk.

48:54.224 --> 48:57.978
Why, you have done me
many a good turn.

48:58.145 --> 49:00.147
Good and ill.

49:01.231 --> 49:05.027
We're like the wind -
we blows both ways.

49:05.193 --> 49:07.529
Aye.

49:17.748 --> 49:20.083
Oh!

49:22.961 --> 49:27.382
Will you take my hand,
Essie Macgowan?

49:39.853 --> 49:43.023
<i>She was still warm
when they found her,</i>

49:43.190 --> 49:45.734
<i>although the life
had fled her body</i>

49:45.901 --> 49:49.071
<i>and only half the apples
were peeled.</i>
